<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>

  <title>Current-State Architecture | Apex Operational Systems</title>

  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
      background: #0b0f14;
      color: #f5f5f5;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .hero, .section {
      max-width: 1180px;
      margin: 50px auto;
      padding: 50px;
      background: linear-gradient(145deg, #171c22, #11161c);
      border: 1px solid #2a2f36;
      border-radius: 20px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
    }

    .hero {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 40px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 52px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    h2 {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 40px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    h3 {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    p {
      color: #d6d6d6;
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    .subtitle, .section-intro {
      text-align: center;
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto 35px;
      color: #d4d4d4;
      font-size: 19px;
    }

    .badge {
      display: inline-block;
      background: #3b2f10;
      color: #ffd36e;
      padding: 8px 16px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 25px;
    }

    .buttons {
      margin-top: 35px;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 20px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .button {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0066d9, #0051b8);
      color: white;
      padding: 14px 28px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 700;
      display: inline-block;
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }

    .button:hover {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a74ff, #0060d6);
      transform: translateY(-3px);
    }

    .diagram-wrapper {
      background: #ffffff;
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 25px;
      overflow-x: auto;
      margin-top: 35px;
    }

    .architecture-diagram {
      width: 100%;
      min-width: 900px;
      height: auto;
      display: block;
    }

    .grid, .pain-points-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 22px;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .two-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 24px;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .card, .pain-card {
      background: #1d232b;
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 24px;
      border: 1px solid #30363f;
      transition: transform 0.25s ease, border-color 0.25s ease;
    }

    .card:hover, .pain-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-6px);
      border-color: #4ea1ff;
    }

    .pain-card {
      border-left: 4px solid #ff6b6b;
    }

    .pain-card h3 {
      color: #ffffff;
      font-size: 22px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .pain-card strong {
      color: #ffd36e;
    }

    .impact {
      border-left: 4px solid #ffd36e;
    }

    .opportunity {
      border-left: 4px solid #8ef0b9;
    }

    .note {
      background: #111820;
      border: 1px solid #2e3947;
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 24px;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }

    footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 40px;
      color: #9ca3af;
      border-top: 1px solid #2b2f35;
      margin-top: 60px;
    }

    footer a {
      color: #4ea1ff;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    @media (max-width: 850px) {
      .hero, .section {
        margin: 30px 16px;
        padding: 30px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 36px;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: 30px;
      }

      .grid,
      .pain-points-grid,
      .two-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="badge">Current-State Architecture</div>

    <h1>Legacy Fulfilment Platform Assessment</h1>

    <p class="subtitle">
      Current-state architecture for a legacy enterprise fulfilment environment with tightly coupled systems,
      manual recovery processes, limited observability, and reactive operational support.
    </p>

    <div class="buttons">
      <a href="index.html" class="button">← Back to Portfolio</a>
      <a href="case-study.html" class="button">View Case Study</a>
      <a href="target-architecture.html" class="button">Target AWS Architecture</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Architecture Overview</h2>

    <p class="section-intro">
      This diagram shows the current operational platform flow from external customer systems through the fulfilment platform,
      database, messaging layer, robot control system, robotic fleet, reporting, log search, and manual support model.
    </p>

    <div class="diagram-wrapper">
      <img
        src="assets/diagrams/Current-State-Master.svg"
        alt="Current-State Fulfilment Platform Architecture"
        class="architecture-diagram">
    </div>

    <div class="note">
      <p>
        The diagram is intentionally modelled as a current-state view rather than an ideal architecture. It highlights
        the operational reality: critical fulfilment workflows depend on tightly coupled systems, manual recovery,
        fragmented investigation paths, and site-reported incidents.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Key Operational Risks Identified</h2>

    <p class="section-intro">
      These pain points map directly to the architecture layers affected by current operational instability.
    </p>

    <div class="pain-points-grid">

      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>🔴 SQL Database Timeouts</h3>
        <p><strong>Affected Layer:</strong> SQL Operational Database</p>
        <p>Reporting failures, slow transactions and operational delays.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>🔴 RabbitMQ Queue Backlogs</h3>
        <p><strong>Affected Layer:</strong> Messaging Layer</p>
        <p>Delayed communication between fulfilment services and robotics.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>🔴 Allocation Lock Exceptions</h3>
        <p><strong>Affected Layer:</strong> Order Fulfilment Platform</p>
        <p>Order processing interruptions and fulfilment delays.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>🔴 Drive Capacity Issues</h3>
        <p><strong>Affected Layer:</strong> Platform & Database Infrastructure</p>
        <p>Server degradation, service instability and emergency operational intervention.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>🔴 Robot Task Idling</h3>
        <p><strong>Affected Layer:</strong> Robot Control System</p>
        <p>Network and application communication failures impacting fulfilment throughput.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>🔴 No Proactive Monitoring</h3>
        <p><strong>Affected Layer:</strong> Operational Support Model</p>
        <p>Issues are identified by site personnel after failure occurs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>🔴 Manual Failover & Recovery</h3>
        <p><strong>Affected Layer:</strong> Operational Support Model</p>
        <p>Recovery activities rely heavily on manual intervention and individual knowledge.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>🔴 Manual Hotfixes</h3>
        <p><strong>Affected Layer:</strong> Release & Change Management</p>
        <p>Production fixes are manually coordinated, increasing validation and rollback risk.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>🔴 No CI/CD Release Pipeline</h3>
        <p><strong>Affected Layer:</strong> Release & Change Management</p>
        <p>Hotfix deployment, validation and rollback activities are not handled through a clear automated pipeline.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Business Impact</h2>

    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card impact">
        <h3>Delayed Customer Deliveries</h3>
        <p>Fulfilment disruption can delay order picking, shipping preparation, and customer delivery timelines.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card impact">
        <h3>Reduced Operational Throughput</h3>
        <p>Database, messaging, robotic control, and network issues can reduce the volume of orders processed.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card impact">
        <h3>Increased Downtime Cost</h3>
        <p>Manual recovery and unclear failover processes extend service disruption during high-severity incidents.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card impact">
        <h3>High Support Burden</h3>
        <p>Support teams spend significant time investigating recurring issues rather than improving platform resilience.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card impact">
        <h3>Slow Incident Resolution</h3>
        <p>Limited observability, fragmented logs, and knowledge silos slow down root cause analysis.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card impact">
        <h3>Operational Risk During Peak Periods</h3>
        <p>Scalability constraints, database bottlenecks, and manual processes increase risk during high-volume periods.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Why Transformation Is Required</h2>

    <p class="section-intro">
      The current architecture supports fulfilment operations, but its resilience and operational maturity are limited by
      legacy infrastructure, manual recovery processes, reactive support, and limited monitoring.
    </p>

    <div class="two-grid">
      <div class="card opportunity">
        <h3>Move from Reactive to Proactive Operations</h3>
        <p>Introduce centralised monitoring, alerting, dashboards, log correlation, and operational intelligence.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card opportunity">
        <h3>Improve Resilience & Recovery</h3>
        <p>Reduce manual failover dependency with better backup, recovery, availability, and disaster recovery design.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card opportunity">
        <h3>Modernise Infrastructure</h3>
        <p>Move toward scalable cloud infrastructure with improved capacity management and reduced server maintenance overhead.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card opportunity">
        <h3>Enable AI-Assisted Support</h3>
        <p>Use AI to retrieve knowledge, correlate incidents, summarise logs, suggest runbooks, and support faster investigations.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="buttons">
      <a href="target-architecture.html" class="button">View AWS Target Architecture →</a>
      <a href="case-study.html" class="button">Back to Case Study</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <p>
      <a href="index.html">Portfolio</a>
      |
      <a href="case-study.html">Case Study</a>
      |
      <a href="target-architecture.html">Target Architecture</a>
    </p>

    <p>
      Current-State Architecture • Operational Assessment • Cloud Transformation Foundation
    </p>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>
